---Docker basic commands
#To pull image form git hub to host
docker pull ubuntu<imagename>
docker pull centos:centos7
#List all the images
docker images
#List all containers
docker ps -a or docker ps -l
#To search Docker image
docker image search image[image:tag]
For eg.
docker image search centos:centos7
#docker image search centos:centos7
#To built your image
#docker build -t imagename:tag
For eg.
docker build -t tom:1.0

docker rmi ubuntu<imagename> -- to remove the image
docker start <imageid> --run the container with the command that was used to create it
docker ps -l and docker ps -a --to see all the docker run or exited
docker stop dockerid/auto-name
**************
creating a docker file:-
it contians instruction to builing a docker image.
instrucions contains various keywords.
7)From -> indicates the base image from which the container is built
8)RUN --> This indicates the command that need to be executed on the image
9)docker buit -t imagename:tag --to build an image
10) docker run --name "container-name" -p<hostport>:<continerport><imagename:tage>
11) docker info --provide wide info like taken size kernel version etc

12) docker rm <containername>/id --to remove container
13) docker rmi <imageid>
not delete the runing conainer
first we have to stop the container
14) docker kill did to kill process
15) ctrl+p+q to quit form the container withoud terminating it


16) docker run -it centos bash
interactively connect to container shell

